sentences.english: At midnight my brother and nephew went to get fuel.
sentences.chinese: 大半夜里，我哥哥和外甥去弄燃油。

sentences.english: Talent is merely success’s distant cousin.
sentences.chinese: 而天赋只是成功的远房外甥。

sentences.english: I give you joy, my dear niece.
sentences.chinese: 我向你道喜，亲爱的外甥女。

sentences.english: She to Tai'an 3 to send her niece to go to university.
sentences.chinese: 她3号去泰安送她升入大学的外甥女去了。

sentences.english: But among them , his nephew , misfitted , felt that he was going to die .
sentences.chinese: 可是在他们中间，他的外甥却落落寡欢，甚至想到死。

sentences.english: Today, I was babysitting my nephew.
sentences.chinese: 今天我在家照看我的小外甥。

sentences.english: His name had never been voluntarily mentioned before them by her niece; and the kind of half-expectation which Mrs.
sentences.chinese: 外甥女儿从来没有主动在舅父母面前提起过他的名字。

sentences.english: It was the voice of Scrooge's nephew Fred.
sentences.chinese: 这是斯克鲁奇外甥弗雷德的声音。

sentences.english: Lottie was certainly better off without nieces and nephews to feel sorry for.
sentences.chinese: 珞蒂好多了，不必看着苦兮兮的外甥们，替他们可怜。

sentences.english: The third, their niece Rajani, was 5.
sentences.chinese: 第三个小女孩是她们的外甥女，只有5岁。

sentences.english: My little nephew sticks to his mom twenty-four seven.
sentences.chinese: 我的小外甥一天到晚都黏著他妈妈。

sentences.english: Don't hoax the new boy who's my nephew.
sentences.chinese: 别戏弄新来的小伙子啊，他是我外甥。

sentences.english: His hand shook too, as he clinked his glass against his nephew's.
sentences.chinese: 当他和外甥碰杯时，他的手也哆嗦了。

sentences.english: The sixth confirmed case is the 10-year-old nephew of the initial case.
sentences.chinese: 第6例确诊病例为该最初病例的10岁外甥。

sentences.english: My nephew,George,has a money box but it is always empty.
sentences.chinese: 我的外甥乔治有一个存钱罐，可里面老是空空如也。
高文爵士是亚瑟王的外甥。

definition: younger male cousin via female line
son of a male cousin via female line
daughter's son/grandson/descendant via the female line

Sun Tzu, also known as Sun Wu 孫武|孙武[Sun1 Wu3] (c. 500 BC, dates of birth and death uncertain), general, strategist and philosopher of the Spring and Autumn Period (700-475 BC), believed to be the author of the “Art of War” 孫子兵法|孙子兵法[Sun1 zi3 Bing1 fa3], one of the Seven Military Classics of ancient China 武經七書|武经七书[Wu3 jing1 Qi1 shu1]
